def: The bark, or a vegetable extract brought in solid cakes fromSouth America and believed to be derived from the bark, of the treeChrysophyllum glycyphloeum. It is used as an alterative andastringent.
Not capable or susceptible of effervescence.
The state, character, or privileges of an heir; right ofinheriting. Heirship movables, certain kinds of movables which theheir is entitled to take, besides the heritable estate. [Scot.]
In a grounded or firmly established manner. Glanvill.
To transfer the title of from one to another; to alienate.

A genus of evergreen shrubs from the Cape of Good Hope, havinghandsome foliage. Leucadendron argenteum is the silverboom of thecolonists.
A woman who attends to a dairy.
One who considers; a man of reflection; a thinker. Milton.
